-- Brazil Government Had 2 Billion Reais Primary Surplus in Dec.
-- B y   A r n a l d o   G a l v a o
-- 2012-01-27T16:05:04Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-27/brazil-government-had-2-billion-reais-primary-surplus-in-dec-.html
Brazil ’s central government posted a
primary surplus, excluding interest payments, of 2 billion reais
($1.1 billion) in December, the Treasury said.  The central government’s surplus excluding interest
payments comes after a revised 4.71 billion reais surplus in
November, the Treasury said in a statement distributed in
Brasilia today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
